definitions.definition: (biblical) A king of Israel mentioned in the second book of Kings.
(biblical) A book of the Old Testament and the Hebrew Tanakh.
(biblical) A Hebrew prophet traditionally considered the author of the Book of Zechariah, the eleventh of the Twelve Minor Prophets.
(biblical) A Hebrew priest, the father of John the Baptist.
A male given name from Hebrew
